@3v1n0 Thanks! I'm sorry it took so long to get around to this, but I've finally merged !866 and rebased this one. While I was doing so, I updated any coding style points that have changed since the MR was created.

Despite the delay, I'm quite excited about this one; now that it's not tangled up with the other MR it's much easier to see that it's a very interesting improvement.

So it looks like you tried several approaches, documented in the several different commits, before settling on the final one. Do you recommend that we squash the commits together, in the end? At least squashing the first two seems like it might be a good idea because there are some changes made to the test files that are reverted in the second commit.

